00:35:05,020 --> 00:35:06,798
the treatment plan now,
Bobby could be ready

760
00:35:06,822 --> 00:35:07,999
to play by midseason next year.

761
00:35:08,023 --> 00:35:10,056
<i>- Next season?</i>
- Yes.

762
00:35:10,125 --> 00:35:11,536
<i>So you're telling me
Bobby's gonna miss</i>

763
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:13,421
<i>this postseason and
most of next season?</i>

764
00:35:13,445 --> 00:35:14,755
- Yes.<i>
- This might have been his last shot</i>

765
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:15,899
<i>to play in the Series.</i>

766
00:35:15,981 --> 00:35:17,964
<i>He's gonna be devastated.</i>

767
00:35:18,033 --> 00:35:19,299
I'm sorry.

768
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:20,911
<i>I, uh... If only I could
tell him in person,</i>

769
00:35:20,935 --> 00:35:23,214
<i>but I got Banksy waiting
in a Seattle hotel room</i>

770
00:35:23,238 --> 00:35:24,804
<i>with carpal tunnel.</i>

771
00:35:28,994 --> 00:35:31,010
If you want, I could
tell the patient.

772
00:35:31,079 --> 00:35:33,663
<i>Yeah? Oh, that'd be
great, and then I'll follow up.</i>

773
00:35:33,732 --> 00:35:35,772
<i>Devon, next time
you're in New York,</i>

774
00:35:35,833 --> 00:35:37,028
<i>you're sitting with
me at a Knicks game.</i>

775
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:38,412
Oh, great. I'm a big Knicks fan.

776
00:35:38,436 --> 00:35:39,630
<i>You're not a Knicks fan?</i>

777
00:35:39,654 --> 00:35:41,771
No, no. I said I<i> am</i>
a big Knicks fan.

778
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,401
<i>- That's too bad, 'cause they're courtside.</i>
- No, wait.

779
00:35:43,425 --> 00:35:45,169
<i>Listen, they're telling
me I got to shut this down.</i>

780
00:35:45,193 --> 00:35:47,727
- No, wait. Wait, wait, wait.
<i>- Thanks.</i>

781
00:35:47,813 --> 00:35:48,995
Massero.

782
00:35:49,064 --> 00:35:51,748
Welcome to the club.

783
00:35:51,817 --> 00:35:53,032
You just got Smoothed.

784
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:57,820
We have to tell Bobby
Singer that his season is over?

785
00:35:57,889 --> 00:35:59,806
No. Not we. You.

786
00:36:02,661 --> 00:36:05,094
Hey, Conrad.

787
00:36:05,164 --> 00:36:06,762
Massero doesn't want a resident

788
00:36:06,832 --> 00:36:09,899
telling Bobby the bad
news. He could go off on us.

789
00:36:09,952 --> 00:36:11,529
Massero wouldn't
care if a candy striper

790
00:36:11,553 --> 00:36:14,137
told Bobby the bad news,
as long as it wasn't Massero.

791
00:36:22,548 --> 00:36:25,181
Hey.

792
00:36:25,250 --> 00:36:27,517
I found four new
patients of Lane Hunter.

793
00:36:27,586 --> 00:36:29,052
You're kidding. How?

794
00:36:29,104 --> 00:36:31,237
Social media. I was
able to flag posts

795
00:36:31,306 --> 00:36:32,705
from five new cancer patients

796
00:36:32,774 --> 00:36:34,352
asking for prayers for
their upcoming treatments

797
00:36:34,376 --> 00:36:36,075
at Lane's clinic.

798
00:36:36,144 --> 00:36:38,144
- You're amazing.
- I kind of am.

799
00:36:38,213 --> 00:36:39,841
I'll get contact
info on the patients

800
00:36:39,865 --> 00:36:41,142
and call them saying I'm working

801
00:36:41,166 --> 00:36:43,182
on the cluster story and ask

802
00:36:43,251 --> 00:36:45,196
about their treatment
regimen with their oncologist.

803
00:36:45,220 --> 00:36:48,254
Good, but keep this on the DL.

804
00:36:48,323 --> 00:36:50,200
We don't want to make
anyone suspicious.

805
00:36:50,224 --> 00:36:52,458
Suspicious of Lane?

806
00:36:52,527 --> 00:36:55,212
Should they be?

807
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:57,163
Devon, you know how much

808
00:36:57,249 --> 00:36:58,397
I respect what you do

809
00:36:58,466 --> 00:37:00,650
for a living.

810
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:02,346
But if there's a story
here, I'll chase it.

811
00:37:02,370 --> 00:37:03,953
There's no turning back.

812
00:37:04,006 --> 00:37:06,906
You understand?

813
00:37:10,912 --> 00:37:12,846
Go for it.

814
00:37:12,931 --> 00:37:14,542
You will eventually be
working there with me

815
00:37:14,566 --> 00:37:16,326
- in surgery...
- Randolph.

816
00:37:16,351 --> 00:37:18,351
Yeah? Excuse me for a second.

817
00:37:18,420 --> 00:37:20,520
I've spoken with Massero.

818
00:37:20,606 --> 00:37:22,216
According to the Chinese
government, no doctor

819
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:24,085
below an attending can
assist in the operation.

820
00:37:24,109 --> 00:37:25,508
That means no residents.

821
00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:27,210
Are you okay with that?

822
00:37:27,279 --> 00:37:29,095
Of course. Why wouldn't I?

823
00:37:29,164 --> 00:37:30,164
Good.

824
00:37:32,251 --> 00:37:34,217
Excuse me.

825
00:37:34,286 --> 00:37:36,920
Listen, we'll
pick this up later.

826
00:37:42,127 --> 00:37:43,954
Bobby, you're not
gonna be able to play.

827
00:37:43,978 --> 00:37:46,145
A contusion

828
00:37:46,214 --> 00:37:48,076
from a hard-hit ball while
you're on blood thinners

829
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:51,117
could cause internal
bleeding, and you could die.

830
00:37:51,186 --> 00:37:54,086
So that's it, huh?

831
00:37:56,275 --> 00:37:58,675
It all ends here.

832
00:37:58,727 --> 00:38:01,061
No. No, not necessarily.

833
00:38:01,146 --> 00:38:03,346
It is not unrealistic to think

834
00:38:03,414 --> 00:38:06,249
that you could be back
midseason next year.

835
00:38:06,317 --> 00:38:07,834
But...

836
00:38:07,903 --> 00:38:10,169
I'll be 38.

837
00:38:10,238 --> 00:38:13,139
This was supposed
to be my last season.

838
00:38:17,311 --> 00:38:19,245
Didn't Massero tell you that?

839
00:38:21,333 --> 00:38:22,932
No.

840
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,284
No, he didn't.

841
00:38:27,088 --> 00:38:28,287
All right.

842
00:38:28,356 --> 00:38:30,222
Okay.

843
00:38:30,291 --> 00:38:33,226
All right, so when can I
start having sex again?

844
00:38:35,446 --> 00:38:36,879
Four to five weeks.

845
00:38:36,932 --> 00:38:40,016
Oh, and by the way,
somebody wants to see you.

846
00:38:45,039 --> 00:38:48,374
Do you really think women
are turned on by stuff like this?

847
00:38:48,443 --> 00:38:49,987
I mean, come on,
you guys are the ones

848
00:38:50,011 --> 00:38:51,572
who are fascinated
with body parts, not us.

849
00:38:51,596 --> 00:38:55,181
But you know who does
get turned on by them?

850
00:38:55,250 --> 00:38:56,649
Gossip Web sites.

851
00:38:56,718 --> 00:38:58,562
So, if you send
one of these to me

852
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:00,848
or one of my colleagues
again, I will blast this picture out

853
00:39:00,872 --> 00:39:02,817
with your name on
it to<i> Page Six, TMZ,</i>

854
00:39:02,841 --> 00:39:05,341
<i>The New Yorker, Deadspin...</i>
you see where I'm going with this?

855
00:39:05,410 --> 00:39:06,976
Yeah.

856
00:39:08,964 --> 00:39:11,214
I'm sorry.

857
00:39:11,282 --> 00:39:13,916
Good.

858
00:39:13,985 --> 00:39:15,385
It's a start.

859
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:20,668
<i>Time for your radiation mapping,</i>

860
00:39:20,692 --> 00:39:22,325
Mr. Phillips.

861
00:39:22,394 --> 00:39:24,177
I'm ready, I guess.

862
00:39:26,348 --> 00:39:28,297
Honey, relax.

863
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:29,799
I'll be fine.

864
00:39:29,868 --> 00:39:32,334
What could go wrong?

865
00:39:41,396 --> 00:39:44,831
Well, I guess if I get
more time with Mary,

866
00:39:44,899 --> 00:39:47,150
- this will all be worth it.
- But will it?

867
00:39:47,219 --> 00:39:51,237
Dr. Hunter says we can
increase his survival time 25%.

868
00:39:51,305 --> 00:39:54,457
What does 25%
longer survival mean?

869
00:39:54,526 --> 00:39:56,275
Months? Years?

870
00:39:56,344 --> 00:39:58,911
It's an estimate based on
patients with similar cancers

871
00:39:58,980 --> 00:40:01,447
using Dr. Hunter's protocol.

872
00:40:01,515 --> 00:40:04,116
She's saying they lived
an additional five weeks.

873
00:40:04,186 --> 00:40:05,429
Five weeks? Stop this thing.

874
00:40:05,453 --> 00:40:09,188
Someone has to
talk to me straight.

875
00:40:09,274 --> 00:40:11,057
You're elected.

876
00:40:11,125 --> 00:40:12,525
Give me a sec, guys.

877
00:40:14,445 --> 00:40:16,179
Dr. Hunter could be talking

878
00:40:16,248 --> 00:40:18,059
about new radiation techniques
that I don't know about.

879
00:40:18,083 --> 00:40:21,884
I'm an internist, but all
treatments and tests have risk.

880
00:40:21,953 --> 00:40:23,886
Chemo and radiation are toxic.

881
00:40:23,955 --> 00:40:25,349
They have to be,
to kill the cancer.

882
00:40:25,373 --> 00:40:28,091
Just tell me if these treatments
will make me die sooner.

883
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:31,994
They will make you
feel sicker, nauseous,

884
00:40:32,047 --> 00:40:33,757
and will weaken
your immune system

885
00:40:33,781 --> 00:40:36,883
and that means you're more
in danger of getting infections.

886
00:40:36,968 --> 00:40:41,153
And some of those
infections can kill you.

887
00:40:41,223 --> 00:40:42,699
Why didn't anybody
tell us this before?

888
00:40:42,723 --> 00:40:46,459
No one wants to
take away hope, Mary.

889
00:40:48,563 --> 00:40:51,264
What would you
do if you were me?

890
00:40:53,568 --> 00:40:56,069
I wouldn't want to
spend the time I have left

891
00:40:56,154 --> 00:40:57,903
at Dr. Hunter's clinic.

892
00:40:57,989 --> 00:41:00,270
I'd want to spend every
minute I have left with her.

893
00:41:05,046 --> 00:41:07,079
Start the paperwork now.

894
00:41:07,148 --> 00:41:09,348
Discharge me or I'll
walk out of here myself.

895
00:41:09,417 --> 00:41:11,417
Honey, you can't do that.

896
00:41:11,503 --> 00:41:13,469
Can he?

897
00:41:13,538 --> 00:41:15,021
It's a hospital, not a prison.

898
00:41:15,089 --> 00:41:16,451
We can't hold
him against his will.

899
00:41:16,475 --> 00:41:19,909
It's called eloping,

900
00:41:19,978 --> 00:41:23,179
when a patient slips away
without being discharged.

901
00:41:27,319 --> 00:41:30,453
What about this,
uh, chest tube thing?

902
00:41:30,522 --> 00:41:33,389
Well, we changed you
to a portable system

903
00:41:33,457 --> 00:41:36,392
to make it easier for you
here. Mary knows how it works.

904
00:41:36,444 --> 00:41:39,478
It's easy and your
dressing is changed, so...

905
00:41:39,547 --> 00:41:40,730
you're good to go.

906
00:41:40,798 --> 00:41:42,510
We're gonna have
Hospice check on you

907
00:41:42,534 --> 00:41:43,900
when you're settled back home

908
00:41:43,968 --> 00:41:46,552
if you choose to leave now.

909
00:41:46,620 --> 00:41:50,489
Honey, what do you think?

910
00:41:50,558 --> 00:41:53,376
That garage ain't
gonna clean itself.

911
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:55,395
It's been fun.

912
00:41:55,463 --> 00:41:57,024
Come on. Wait, wait, wait, wait.

913
00:41:57,048 --> 00:41:59,448
- Take that off.
- Help Mr. Phillips back to his room

914
00:41:59,518 --> 00:42:01,718
- and take out his IV, please.
- Easy, easy, easy.

915
00:42:02,787 --> 00:42:04,470
- You all right?
- Yeah.

916
00:42:11,146 --> 00:42:12,478
Thank you.

917
00:42:13,548 --> 00:42:15,648
Oh, uh, by the way,

918
00:42:15,716 --> 00:42:17,416
you two make a very cute couple.

919
00:42:17,485 --> 00:42:20,052
Hustle, Mary. In
case you missed it,

920
00:42:20,121 --> 00:42:24,156
my end of the hourglass
is very low on sand.

921
00:42:24,225 --> 00:42:26,185
Shut up or I'll
leave you right here.

922
00:42:36,137 --> 00:42:38,020
I slept with Noni.

923
00:42:40,024 --> 00:42:43,543
Well, I haven't slept with Jude.

924
00:42:43,611 --> 00:42:45,762
Maybe I did it to get over you.

925
00:42:45,830 --> 00:42:48,531
That kind of sucks for Noni.

926
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,566
No, she's fine
with it. Believe me.

927
00:42:50,635 --> 00:42:53,319
So, how'd that work out for you?

928
00:42:53,405 --> 00:42:57,189
What do you think?

929
00:43:06,868 --> 00:43:09,234
Dr. Lane Hunter.

930
00:43:11,205 --> 00:43:12,571
What about her?

931
00:43:14,508 --> 00:43:16,659
Tell me everything.

